Here’s an example of a simple HTML web app that takes the concept of "Random Mom Jokes" and structures it as a single HTML file with embedded CSS and JavaScript. Since I don't have access to browse external URLs, I’ll create a sample collection of mom jokes for demonstration purposes. You can replace the jokes with any you prefer.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Random Mom Jokes</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            background-color: #f1f1f1;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .container {
            text-align: center;
            background-color: white;
            padding: 20px;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
            max-width: 400px;
        }
        h1 {
            font-size: 24px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        .joke {
            font-size: 18px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
        }
        button {
            padding: 10px 15px;
            font-size: 16px;
            cursor: pointer;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #008CBA;
            color: white;
        }
        button:hover {
            background-color: #005f6b;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="container">
    <h1>Random Mom Jokes</h1>
    <div class="joke" id="joke">Click the button for a joke!</div>
    <button onclick="newJoke()">Get Joke</button>
</div>

<script>
    const jokes = [
        "I told my kids I was going to freeze their toys so they wouldn't have to share. Now I have to find a way to unfreeze them!",
        "Why did the computer go to the doctor? Because it had a virus... just like my kids during flu season!",
        "I'm not a regular mom, I'm a cool mom. Just kidding—please wear your helmets!",
        "Why did the mom sit on the clock? Because she wanted to be on time!",
        "I asked my mom to help me with my math homework, but she just said 'Mom-ing is hard enough!'"
    ];

    function newJoke() {
        const jokeElement = document.getElementById('joke');
        const randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
        jokeElement.textContent = jokes[randomIndex];
    }
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

1. **HTML Structure**: 
   - A basic structure with a title, a container that holds a heading, a display area for jokes, and a button to fetch a new joke.

2. **Styling (CSS)**: 
   - The container is styled to be centered on the page with some basic padding, background color, and shadow effects for aesthetics.

3. **JavaScript Functionality**: 
   - An array of mom jokes is defined, and a function `newJoke()` picks a random joke from this array and updates the displayed joke when the button is clicked.

You can copy this code into an `.html` file and open it in any web browser to see the random mom jokes web app in action. Feel free to replace the jokes in the array with your favorites!
